Introduction

Yoshi is the main rapper of YG Entertainment's boy group TREASURE.

In 2018, Yoshi participated in YG Entertainment's new survival show, YG Treasure Box. At first, he was not selected for the main group, TREASURE, however, on January 29, 2019, YGE announced that he would form a second group from the show, called MAGNUM, and he was one of the members. The groups would promote together as TREASURE 13, and also eventually separated as two units.

Unfortunately, due to scandals surrounding the agency, the debut was postponed.

On January 6, YGE posted a notice on their official website stating the group's future plans. This included re-organizing as a 12-member group and the integration of the two units, TREASURE and MAGNUM, into only one group named simply as TREASURE.

Yoshi debuted as a member of TREASURE on August 7, 2020 with their first single album "THE FIRST STEP: CHAPTER ONE".
